# English-only project language

Write and maintain **all** of the following in **English**:

- README and docs under `doc/`
- Module/class/function docstrings
- Inline code comments
- Commit messages and PR descriptions (when contributing)
- User-facing CLI help strings and log messages in library code
- `AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/rules/` content
- All files under `doc/` (including `doc/TESTING.md`)

Do **not** add documentation README files under `src/test/` or `src/main/`; use `doc/` instead.

## Exceptions

- **Locale-specific data or templates** (e.g. Chinese text inside a generated birth-certificate document) may stay in the target language; add a short English comment explaining why.
- **Third-party file names** — do not rename files on disk unless asked.
- **Private resources** under `src/main/resources/private/` are not versioned.

## Style

- Prefer clear, concise technical English (US spelling is fine).
- Keep bilingual *tags* out of docstrings; use English only.
- When editing existing Chinese text in docs or comments, translate it rather than leaving mixed language.
